\underline{d(x,y)}=d(x,y) + d(x,x)+d(y,y)\underline{\geq d(y,x)}+d(y,y)\underline{\geq d(x,y)}.
2d(x,y)=d(x,y)+d(x,y)\geq d(y,y)=0\implies d(x,y)\geq 0.
